  "texts": [
    "As illustrated in Figure 1, each block consists of five elements: the up and down edges indicate vertical positioning, the left and right edges denote horizontal positioning, and the level represents depth positioning within the K stacked tables, with each table corresponding to a specific relation.",
    "Via our proposed Blk-DDM (described in Section 3.2), these M blocks are progressively refined to reveal the recognized triples.",
    "The proposed decoding scheme, named Parallel Boundary Emitting Strategy (PBES), is introduced to extract triples from the blocks.",
    "PBES follows the four edges and one level of each block, emitting them in parallel to the corresponding entities and relation.",
    "Specifically, for each block, the up and down edges are extended to the left side of the table, indicating the boundaries of the head entity."
  ],
